This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) category as it proposes a variant of momentum optimization, which is a widely used technique in deep learning. Additionally, the paper provides theoretical convergence bounds for online convex optimization, which is a common problem in machine learning. 

The paper also involves numerical optimization (cs.NA) as it deals with gradient-based optimization methods. 

Computer vision (cs.CV) is another possible category as momentum optimization is commonly used in image classification and object detection tasks. 

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is a broad category that encompasses machine learning and optimization, making it a likely candidate. 

Finally, data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) could be a possible category as the paper proposes a new algorithmic variant of momentum optimization.
